Farcon Creators Scholarship applications are now live!

show_title: GM Farcaster ep237 Wednesday April 23, 2025 with Octant and @vpabundance
text:
Okay I am actually liking farcaster.

So many interesting stories of random people, interaction in comments, and it feels like a genuine place.

Feels like the old internet: not overcrowded, genuine stories, lot's of niche discussions.

The channels are a goldmine as well: recently discovered gardening and might start having plants myself too.

I even started meeting ppl irl from farcaster!

So far was very interesting to be a lurker on farcaster. Still don't understand the algo and it's to write posts that get noticed, but maybe my posts just suck and are not for this space.

But so far farcaster has been good, MUCH better than a year ago

cast.text: Reminds me of when I lived in Alaska

text:
üëÅÔ∏èüéôÔ∏è Today at 2PM PT, we launch the Based Creators Directory live on stream. Tune in to the 1st episode of The Based Creators Show, now broadcasting from x.com/buildonbase & /base-creators every Wednesday.

Register here: https://lu.ma/7l2x8lhv

With this first episode, we celebrate the official launch for the Based Creators Directory mini app, a free resource to bring more visibility & opportunities to creators on base.

We will introduce @coordinape, the community dev team behind the Based Creators Directory, & learn how interoperable onchain creator profiles have the potential to scale the creator ecosystem.

We'll get to hear from @statuette, @ted, & @coinbrad.eth on their goals for onchain creator support, & discuss how Farcaster, @base.base.eth & @baseapp.base.eth will play a vital role in discovery & amplification of onchain creativity.

Hosted by @thecreators @lynn-mosqueda @rachelonchain.eth @s-mok-e @tonchu @defiginger @zemm @ashmbanks and presented by @coordinape @ownthedoge @basedfarcast
